        "content": "<p>Coercions are eagerly unfolded, so it sees <code>(fun x =&gt; 3) 0</code> and immediately reduces it to <code>3</code> and it no longer matches <code>f 0</code>. You should probably use a dedicated coercion function instead:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">coe</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Struct</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">coe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">n₀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Coe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">coe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Struct</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">coe</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then it turns <code>((fun _:ℕ ↦ 3):Struct)</code> into <code>Struct.coe (fun _:ℕ ↦ 3)</code> and it can match just fine</p>",
